-- Generated by that file's PART A against the live database on 2026-07-10, then
-- transcribed verbatim. The only edit: `set` is quoted as `"set"`. Postgres
-- classes SET as an UNRESERVED keyword so quote_ident() left it bare, and bare
-- is legal -- but `"set"` denotes the identical identifier and survives being
-- pasted through tools with a less forgiving parser.
